===Noun===
'''underdog'''

# a [[competitor]] thought [[unlikely]] to [[win]]; somebody at a [[disadvantage]]
# To '''give one underdog''' : to give a high swing usually given by parent to child. Pushing hard from the back, so high that the parent can run under the swing and appear at the front.


